other_tests.findings: Pathological examination showed a 1.5-cm grade 3 invasive ductal carcinoma that did not overexpress the estrogen receptor (ER) or progesterone receptor (PR) and did not express human epidermal growth factor receptor 2 (HER2) (i.e., it was triple-negative). Seven axillary nodes contained metastatic tumor.
Ms. E was found to have a 5382insC BRCA1 mutation.
Embryo free of the BRCA1 mutation was implanted.
